docs.text: if snake eyes were a dog , you'd put it to sleep .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: if it was a couch , you'd put it out on the sidewalk , where it would sit for a week .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: if it were your child , you'd be reading military school catalogs .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: if it were a ship -- no , it wouldn't be the titanic , that would imply glamor and tragedy -- it would be the exxon valdez .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: ( personal side note : i saw this movie on the road during a houston business trip .
docs.label: negative

docs.label: negative

docs.text: this forced me to pay full price for snake eyes instead of watching a perfectly good baseball game for free -- so the invective , deserved as it is , should be seen in that perspective . )
docs.label: negative

docs.text: snake eyes is supposed to be a mystery movie , and good mystery movies are supposed to leave you asking yourself questions on the way out of theater .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: snake eyes is not a good mystery movie , but i had some questions : where's the manager , and how do i get a re-admit pass ?
docs.label: negative

docs.text: if i fall asleep on the drive home and wreck my rent-a-car , can i sue brian de palma ?
docs.label: negative

docs.text: is it too late for the academy to revoke nicolas cage's oscar ?
docs.label: negative

docs.text: will someone please ( i'm begging you ) give gary sinise a role worthy of his talents ?
docs.label: negative

docs.text: and how , exactly does cage end up wearing the exact same shirt and tie as sinise does ?
docs.label: negative

docs.text: the first and most glaringly wrong thing with snake eyes is the trailer .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: if you've seen the trailer without seeing the movie , consider yourself fortunate .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: the trailer is a work of sheer genius .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: it manages to convey everything worthy of the movie -- the noteworthy steadicam work , the exuberance of cage's performance as a thoroughly corrupt atlantic city policeman , the essential elements of the marginal plot .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: the expert craftsman who pieced together a fairly good trailer out of snippets of a wretched movie deserves praise and a percentage of the gross .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: ( is a best trailer category at the oscars that far-fetched , after all ? )
docs.label: negative

docs.text: but all it does is set us up for an overwhelmingly disappointing movie .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: the trailer sets up what should have been a promising plot : detective ricky santoro ( cage ) must solve the mystery of who shot the secretary of defense at an atlantic city pay-per-view boxing match .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: unfortunately , there are multiple problems afoot .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: the trailer gives away much , too much of the story .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: the shooter is killed instantly , so the story revolves around why the secretary was killed and who is involved in the conspiracy .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: the film's secret is ho-hum at best , and anyone who has watched the trailer and is aware of the law of economy of characters can figure out who the top conspirator is .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: without an interesting plot , without interesting dialogue , and without much of a reason to care about the characters or the story , snake eyes is a failure on almost every possible level .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: as much as i hated this movie , i must give brian de palma one tiny bit of credit .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: de palma is maddeningly inconsistent .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: he can , on his day , create amazingly well-done movies ( the untouchables , carlito's way ) .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: on off-days , he can be , well , just horrid ( the bonfire of the vanities , raising cain ) .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: snake eyes falls into the horrid category , but there are a couple of moments that are worth seeing strictly for their film-school degree-of-difficulty value .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: the steadicam opening scene does a good job of introducing the cage character and is a virtuoso technical job by both the director and the actor .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: there is a split-screen chase scene that looks pretty good , and it's followed by a god's eye view of a bank of hotel rooms that's imaginitively done .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: this is what's called giving the devil his due .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: but the technical skill doesn't even come close to making up for the sheer evil of this movie .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: placing plot holes to one side for a moment , snake eyes features easily the worst boxing match in cinema history ( george foreman is in better shape than the movie boxers ) , a hurricane that exists for no other reason than to punctuate significant plotlines with portentuous thunderclaps , and perhaps the worst , most overly drawn out ending in years .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: snake eyes is a criminal act , an evil waste of time and talent .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: cage , sinise , and yes , even de palma deserve better .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: the audience deserves better -- but no refund , no re-admit pass , no free popcorn coupon , can ever restore to us the time we've spent or wash the awful images from our mind .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: however , we are left with one consolation , that we were warned by the movie's title -- because snake eyes is nothing more than a roll of craps .
docs.label: negative
